  "doc_id": "45776",
  "text": "The original model does not incorporate β-TrCP explicitly. To allow for the investigation of the potential influence of β-TrCP on nuclear NF-κB dynamics, we extended the existing model based on published experimental data. Experimental observations suggest that changes in the concentration of β-TrCP influence IκB degradation. The overexpression of β-TrCP reduced the concentration of IκB by enhancing its proteasomal degradation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . In contrast, the overexpression of a dominant negative mutant of β-TrCP inhibited the proteasomal degradation of IκB [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] . Furthermore, it was shown that the IKK-dependent phosphorylation of IκB is a prerequisite for the β-TrCP-mediated ubiquitination and degradation of IκB. Thus, we presumed β-TrCP to modulate the rates of both IKK-dependent IκB degradation reactions (reaction 8 and reaction 10, Figure 1 ) in our modelling approach.",
